<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1260,1536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,599,1260,1285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Records associated with mangroves:</emphasis>
Bermuda islands, algae on air roots and on the base of the trunks of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,378,1295,1320]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mangle">
<emphasis box="[151,378,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Rhizophora mangle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mahunka" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[445,635,1295,1320]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Avicennia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[445,635,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Avicennia nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A similar colonization is realized on the air roots of the &quot;White Mangrove&quot; (&quot;Buttonwood&quot;), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fain &amp; Schuster 1983)" authorityName="Fain &amp; Schuster" authorityYear="1983" baseAuthorityName="Fain &amp; Schuster" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[478,962,1332,1357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Conocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erecta">
<emphasis box="[478,691,1333,1356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Conocarpus erecta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[706,953,1332,1357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" refId="ref8850" refString="Fain, A. &amp; Schuster, R. (1983) New astigmatic mites from the coastal area of Bermuda Islands (Acari: Hyadesiidae, Saproglyphidae, Acaridae). Entomologische Mitteilungen des zoologischen Museums Hamburg, 7 (119), 417 - 433." type="journal article">Fain &amp; Schuster 1983</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1260,1536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,545,1367,1392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Records from other habitats:</emphasis>
This species, widespread over the archipelago, lives in the intertidal area and in the lower part of the supralittoral zone of the rocky coast. It is to be found on the rock surface or in micro-fissures, but also on rocks covered by a dense growth of algae or chthamalids from Bermuda islands (
<bibRefCitation pageId="13" pageNumber="234" refId="ref8850" refString="Fain, A. &amp; Schuster, R. (1983) New astigmatic mites from the coastal area of Bermuda Islands (Acari: Hyadesiidae, Saproglyphidae, Acaridae). Entomologische Mitteilungen des zoologischen Museums Hamburg, 7 (119), 417 - 433." type="journal article">Fain &amp; Schuster 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
